An emotional morning for the family of the late Tshegofatso Pule as the court heard painful details of her last moments alive. Tshegofatso's uncle Tumisang Katake says her gruesome death has left the family torn. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - An emotional morning for the family of the late Tshegofatso Pule as the court heard painful details of her last moments alive. Tshegofatso's uncle Tumisang Katake says her gruesome death has left the family torn. Police have confirmed that Pule's boyfriend has been arrested for murder. READ: Tshegofatso Pule's boyfriend arrested The arrest follows a plea and sentence agreement with Muzikayise Malephane, who was sentenced to 20 years in prison for the murder. Pule's body was found hanging from a tree in Roodepoort. "We knew it wasn't going to be easy," Katake said. READ: Memorial held in honour of Tshegofatso Pule "At the end of the day our suspicions have been confirmed. "We suspected from the very onset... that the boyfriend had something to do with it." Katake said babies are raised without fathers. READ: Tshegofatso Pule murder case postponed "Tshegofatso was raised without parents and she turned out okay. "I'm definitely sure Tshegofatso's baby as well was going to turn out okay without the father."